                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L4.xml" title="equivalence relation" addr="jms-00L4" type="local">equivalence relation</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\colon  A\to  A/E]]></fr:tex> be the <html:em>quotient function</html:em> that sends <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> to its equivalence class <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [a\right  ]\mathclose {}}_{E}]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\colon  A\to  A/E]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>jms-00MB/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MB/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="quotients and surjections › forest://jonmsterling/jms-00MB/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MB.xml" title="quotients and surjections" addr="jms-00MB" type="local">quotients and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjections</fr:link></fr:link> › jms-00MB/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We must show that for every equivalence class <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in  A/E]]></fr:tex> there exists an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=u]]></fr:tex>. By definition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u={\mathopen {}\left  [a\right  ]\mathclose {}}_{E}=q{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
